      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHAD'S GIRL (3) got the job done again after leading for her three straight win, scoring by 0.8 lengths (23.36) at Casino over 411m. Still to record a win from this draw but has never missed the frame in two starts. Looks the one to beat. MISS KOBLENZ (8) jumped from out wide and was game in defeat last start when a half a length second (22.25) behind Lara Moon at Ballarat. The form from her last run stacks up well. Hard to beat again. JET FUEL (1) has a moderate overall strike-rate. Hit the board with a minor placing last time when third (22.48) at Gosford. Solid record here at the distance winning two races. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings three times from five attempts. Must be included in calculations. HOOKED ON HOPE (7) is last start winner who looks one of the chances.",
